related_questions.question: What is a snapper?
related_questions.snippet: a. : any of numerous active carnivorous fishes (family Lutjanidae) of warm seas important as food and often as sport fishes. b. : any of several immature fishes (such as the young of the bluefish) that resemble a snapper.
